         <change when="2025-11-28T07:56:34-05:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/saverio">Vote - Accept-Straight-to-Finalization - Outdent l. 16 and 18 before finalization.&#xD;
Since pap. is not opisthographic, I see no need to have &lt;D=.r: delete (?)&#xD;
col. i&#xD;
l. 5 insert space and add accent: [.? ἐ]π̣αοιδή&#xD;
l.  6. add space: [πος(?)] --&gt; [πος (?)]  &#xD;
l. 7 delete underdot: [.?] ̣σ̣ινε --&gt; [.?]σ̣ινε&#xD;
col. ii&#xD;
Why not continuing line numeration, but resumed from 1 in col. ii?&#xD;
l. 3 insert γὰρ, blank space, and move brackets: σ]ὺ&lt;:εἶ θνη[τοῖς] --&gt; σ]ὺ γὰρ εἶ &lt;:θνη[τοῖς]; insert .2 before [.1-2] at the end&#xD;
5.- [λεσον τε]λέαν ἐπαοιδ[ή]ν.&#xD;
l. 6 I think this is wrong markup: it should mean that it has been corrected as Γαδαρηνῆς already since Henrichs. So I’d take it as a spelling correction (but I’m not sure): &lt;:Ταδαρηνῆς|ed|&lt;Γ&gt;αδαρηνῆς=Henrichs:&gt; --&gt; &lt;:Γαδαρηνῆς|corr|Ταδαρηνῆς:&gt;&#xD;
l. 7 even though the GEMF editors leave κατα in the text, they do so because their edition is diplomatic: but it’s a clear repetition (surplus text), and instead of &lt;:κατα|ed|{κατα}:&gt; I would just give{κατα}&#xD;
l.8 should be: 8.- [μα]||ed||κατακατα[.?]=Brashear|κατάκαυ̣μ̣[α]=Henrichs:&gt; &lt;:[*middot*ca.4||ed||[οἶκος]=Eitrem|[παῖς]=Koenen:&gt; μ]υστοδόκ̣ος κατεκα̣[ύθη],&#xD;
l. 9 add comma at the end&#xD;
l. 10 Koenen’s integration &lt;πῦρ δ’ ἐλάφυξεν&gt; (like l. 7 &lt;σεμνοτάτης δὲ θεᾶς&gt; before [παῖς] belong into the commentary (since they are reconstructed hexameters and have nothing to do with the papyrus at issue). Thus, &lt;:ἑπτὰ|ed|&lt;πῦρ δ’ ἐλάφυξεν&gt; ἑπτά=Koenen:&gt; --&gt; just ἑπτά. &#xD;
Same with &lt;κεφαλαὶ ἐφύλαξαν&gt;= post Merkelbach, thus: &lt;:λύκ̣ων||ed||λύ[κ]ω̣ν̣=Henrichs|&lt;κεφαλαὶ ἐφύλαξαν&gt;= post Merkelbach:&gt; --&gt; &lt;:λύκ̣ων|ed|λύ[κ]ω̣ν̣=Henrichs:&gt;&#xD;
ἄρ̣[κων] --&gt; &lt;:ἄρ̣[κων]|ed|ἄρ̣[κτων]=Henrichs:&gt;&#xD;
l. 13 at the end ἔς --&gt; ἔσ&#xD;
l. 14: 14.- βεσαν&#xD;
After l. 14 and 17 forked paragraphos: replace with &gt;---&#xD;
l.18 &lt;:φεύγε|^ι^| δὲ||ed --&gt; &lt;:φεύγε|^ι^| δὲ [.2]||ed;&#xD;
φ̣θ̣[ίνους’ --&gt; φ̣θ̣[ίνουσ’&#xD;
add blank space in Poethke’s restoration: φεύγε|^ι^|δε[.?]=Poethke --&gt; φεύγε|^ι^| δε[.?]=Poethke&#xD;
l. 20 add space + del regularization in apparatus (?): 20.- κοι,&lt;:φεύγ̣[ουσι]{ν}|reg|φεύγ̣[ουσι]ν:&gt; --&gt; 20.- κοι, φεύγ̣[ουσι]{ν}&#xD;
l. 21 add space: 21.- ποι&lt;:.1 --&gt; 21.- ποι &lt;:.1&#xD;
l. 22 add (?) to the reading of SH&#xD;
</change>
         <change when="2023-07-17T16:27:06-04:00"
                 who="http://papyri.info/editor/users/carlosamadorom%C3%A1n">Submit - Sorry, I had deleted the previous version. Please review the text and translation of GEMF 3. Consider the following aspects:&#xD;
There is a problem with the apparatus criticus at line 8 (col. ii): where include these conjectures "[οἶκος] Eitrem : [⟨σεμνοτάτης δὲ⟩ θεᾶς παῖς] Koenen"?.&#xD;
I don't know if lines 16 and 18 (col. ii) must be outdented.&#xD;
Line 18 (col. ii): add "brevis et longa" symbols.</change>
